        <item>
        <title>Introducing Gerayis</title>
        <link>https://blog.leocorporation.dev/2021/03/introducing-gerayis/</link>
        <pubDate>Tue, 09 Mar 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://blog.leocorporation.dev/2021/03/introducing-gerayis/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="https://blog.leocorporation.dev/2021/03/introducing-gerayis/cover.png" alt="Featured image of post Introducing Gerayis" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are starting this month with the release of a new software: Gerayis. Gerayis is the next evolution of Bar Code Generator 2.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s been a few years already since we&amp;rsquo;ve released the first version of Bar Code Generator (at the time, named in french &amp;ldquo;Générateur de codes barre&amp;rdquo;). Then, last year, 2020, we&amp;rsquo;ve released Bar Code Generator 2, with a brand new design, and the possibility to generate QR Codes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The second version main purpose was to deliver to our users, a brand new user experience, while also adding new features.
Gerayis is the next of evolution of Bar Code Generator, with a design and user experience similar to &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://blog.leocorporation.dev/2021/02/introducing-passliss.html&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Passliss&lt;/a&gt;&#39;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.leocorporation.dev/2021/03/introducing-gerayis/cover.png&#34;
	width=&#34;800&#34;
	height=&#34;450&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://blog.leocorporation.dev/2021/03/introducing-gerayis/cover_hu0b071e93705d6c2f85cb089c7ad7697e_32262_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://blog.leocorporation.dev/2021/03/introducing-gerayis/cover_hu0b071e93705d6c2f85cb089c7ad7697e_32262_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;The &amp;ldquo;Bar Code&amp;rdquo; page of Gerayis&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;177&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;426px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;features&#34;&gt;Features&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gerayis has the same features than Bar Code Generator 2, but they are improved, like the QR Code generator which is using a different library than Bar Code Generator 2: &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://www.nuget.org/packages/QRCoder&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;QRCoder&lt;/a&gt;.
Gerayis also includes an improved dark theme and an updated language system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.leocorporation.dev/2021/03/introducing-gerayis/2.png&#34;
	width=&#34;800&#34;
	height=&#34;450&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://blog.leocorporation.dev/2021/03/introducing-gerayis/2_huda3afdd284a24668dc6717a232a58de1_34035_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://blog.leocorporation.dev/2021/03/introducing-gerayis/2_huda3afdd284a24668dc6717a232a58de1_34035_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;The &amp;ldquo;QR Code&amp;rdquo; page of Gerayis&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;177&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;426px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;open-source&#34;&gt;Open Source&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gerayis is Open-Source, and you can check the GitHub repo by &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/Leo-Corporation/Gerayis&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;clicking here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;download&#34;&gt;Download&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://bit.ly/DownloadGerayis&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Click here&lt;/a&gt; to download Gerayis.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
